1
00:00:08,600 --> 00:00:10,961
♪Love's little quiz
takes seven parts sweet♪

2
00:00:10,962 --> 00:00:13,559
♪And three parts bitter,
till you and I meet♪

3
00:00:13,560 --> 00:00:17,159
♪I pretend I'm not there,
but secretly stay♪

4
00:00:17,160 --> 00:00:26,399
♪Waiting for you♪

5
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:31,400
♪We've got so many
romantic dreams to unfold♪

6
00:00:31,480 --> 00:00:36,224
♪Finally hearing
the I love you I long to hold♪

7
00:00:36,225 --> 00:00:39,839
♪Falling fast
into the swirl of your eyes♪

8
00:00:39,840 --> 00:00:42,399
♪It's just too tempting, so tempting♪

9
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:45,499
♪Never could I have guessed♪

10
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:46,499
♪My heart's rhythm♪

11
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:49,632
♪How beautiful it is, meeting you♪

12
00:01:02,975 --> 00:01:05,961
=Late to Love=
(Adapted from "My Husband Is A Billionaire!")

13
00:01:05,962 --> 00:01:08,800
=Episode 6=

14
00:01:09,979 --> 00:01:11,019
Without air conditioning,

15
00:01:11,020 --> 00:01:12,179
aren't you hot?

16
00:01:14,139 --> 00:01:15,379
This is an old apartment complex.

17
00:01:15,380 --> 00:01:17,240
A powerful AC unit
would drive up the electric bill.

18
00:01:19,940 --> 00:01:21,498
What if I reimburse the bill?

19
00:01:21,499 --> 00:01:22,459
Then sure.

20
00:01:28,339 --> 00:01:28,978
Just eat.

21
00:01:28,979 --> 00:01:30,140
Don't be shy.

22
00:01:30,339 --> 00:01:30,858
Make yourself

23
00:01:30,859 --> 00:01:31,659
at home.

24
00:01:31,660 --> 00:01:38,338
♪How did you stay close to me?♪

25
00:01:38,339 --> 00:01:40,140
This is seriously so good.

26
00:01:41,020 --> 00:01:42,299
How are you this good at cooking?

27
00:01:42,300 --> 00:01:44,099
If you like it, eat more.

28
00:01:45,175 --> 00:01:48,019
♪Even though I still believe♪

29
00:01:48,020 --> 00:01:49,099
Is it really that good?

30
00:01:49,100 --> 00:01:50,939
It's amazing.

31
00:01:52,900 --> 00:01:53,611
Have some more.

32
00:01:53,612 --> 00:01:57,745
♪Doesn't mean to say♪

33
00:02:01,240 --> 00:02:02,498
(Product Development Schedule)
Boss,

34
00:02:02,499 --> 00:02:04,218
why are you still here this late?

35
00:02:04,219 --> 00:02:05,379
It's me.

36
00:02:08,860 --> 00:02:09,979
Mr. Zichen?

37
00:02:10,779 --> 00:02:11,740
You…

38
00:02:12,379 --> 00:02:13,938
Didn't Beiyan go on a trip?

39
00:02:13,939 --> 00:02:16,139
I just figured
I'd help lighten his workload.

40
00:02:16,539 --> 00:02:17,620
I see.

41
00:02:21,460 --> 00:02:22,179
You know,

42
00:02:22,180 --> 00:02:23,618
why doesn't Beiyan set his wallpaper

43
00:02:23,619 --> 00:02:24,659
to a picture of his wife?

44
00:02:24,900 --> 00:02:26,538
Mr. Huo's a total workaholic.

45
00:02:26,539 --> 00:02:27,579
He's the type

46
00:02:27,580 --> 00:02:28,739
who keeps work and emotions

47
00:02:28,740 --> 00:02:31,539
completely separate.

48
00:02:33,099 --> 00:02:34,220
That makes sense.

49
00:02:35,619 --> 00:02:36,500
Oh right.

50
00:02:36,580 --> 00:02:39,419
I remember Beiyan used to have
a marriage arrangement with the Ye family.

51
00:02:39,420 --> 00:02:41,699
Before I went abroad, both families
were already discussing it.

52
00:02:41,700 --> 00:02:43,259
But now that he's married,

53
00:02:43,260 --> 00:02:44,620
what happened to them?

54
00:02:45,779 --> 00:02:48,899
Mr. Huo and Miss Ye's engagement
was called off a long time ago.

55
00:02:48,900 --> 00:02:50,819
Probably not long
after you left the country.

56
00:02:51,260 --> 00:02:53,299
The Ye family didn't say much at the time.

57
00:02:53,300 --> 00:02:54,579
Though I heard

58
00:02:54,580 --> 00:02:56,400
Miss Ye was pretty upset.

59
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:58,419
But after that,
she never caused Mr. Huo any trouble.

60
00:02:58,420 --> 00:02:59,019
In that case,

61
00:02:59,020 --> 00:03:00,859
I'll go make you some coffee.

62
00:03:09,580 --> 00:03:12,899
This AI setup of yours
looks way too fake.

63
00:03:12,900 --> 00:03:14,699
Look at us standing by the ocean.

64
00:03:14,700 --> 00:03:16,859
Our expressions are stiff as boards.

65
00:03:17,020 --> 00:03:20,139
And look at your smile. It's like someone
pulled up the corners of your mouth.

66
00:03:20,140 --> 00:03:21,620
One glance and you can tell it's fake.

67
00:03:23,339 --> 00:03:24,659
I'll tweak it a bit more.

68
00:03:31,175 --> 00:03:34,774
♪Sometimes we roll the dice♪

69
00:03:34,775 --> 00:03:38,561
,♪To see what the future hides♪

70
00:03:38,562 --> 00:03:44,745
♪Spinning us round and round
like a never-ending ride♪

71
00:03:45,362 --> 00:03:47,979
♪But I gave you everything♪

72
00:03:47,980 --> 00:03:51,060
You've actually got a pretty cute face.

73
00:03:51,099 --> 00:03:52,220
What did you say?

74
00:03:52,819 --> 00:03:54,259
Your AI controls

75
00:03:54,619 --> 00:03:56,259
are actually really good.

76
00:03:56,499 --> 00:03:57,620
It feels natural.

77
00:03:59,300 --> 00:04:00,539
Here, look.

78
00:04:00,580 --> 00:04:01,659
Anything else look off?

79
00:04:07,860 --> 00:04:10,060
This snowy mountain looks so real.

80
00:04:10,580 --> 00:04:13,379
Almost... too real.

81
00:04:20,179 --> 00:04:21,460
You like snowy mountains?

82
00:04:22,110 --> 00:04:23,778
Back when I was
at the Linhai research lab,

83
00:04:23,779 --> 00:04:25,858
there was a study trip to Europe.

84
00:04:25,859 --> 00:04:27,780
The location was the Alps.

85
00:04:27,940 --> 00:04:29,338
The mountains there

86
00:04:29,339 --> 00:04:30,859
looked exactly like this picture.

87
00:04:31,060 --> 00:04:32,940
Too bad I never got to go.

88
00:04:36,700 --> 00:04:37,899
If you want to go,

89
00:04:37,900 --> 00:04:39,260
you can just tell me.

90
00:04:49,140 --> 00:04:51,179
You...

91
00:04:51,460 --> 00:04:52,900
I...

92
00:04:53,900 --> 00:04:55,338
There are discounted tickets

93
00:04:55,339 --> 00:04:56,820
and a free upgrade.

94
00:04:58,580 --> 00:04:59,298
Not going.

95
00:04:59,299 --> 00:05:00,658
I'm busy.

96
00:05:00,659 --> 00:05:02,978
I'm serious. Miss this chance
and it's gone for good.

97
00:05:02,979 --> 00:05:04,019
I'm serious too.

98
00:05:04,020 --> 00:05:05,019
I'm really busy.

99
00:05:05,020 --> 00:05:05,978
Alright then, Nange.

100
00:05:05,979 --> 00:05:07,220
Don't forget to wash the dishes.

101
00:05:07,419 --> 00:05:08,699
Why am I washing dishes again?

102
00:05:08,700 --> 00:05:10,460
I cook, you wash.

103
00:05:12,140 --> 00:05:13,380
Fine.

104
00:05:13,659 --> 00:05:14,859
What do you want to eat?

105
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:16,659
Braised pork.

106
00:05:16,700 --> 00:05:18,179
Alright, I'll go buy groceries.

107
00:05:19,339 --> 00:05:20,700
Wash the dishes properly.

108
00:05:22,979 --> 00:05:24,739
Xu Nange, open the door!

109
00:05:25,219 --> 00:05:26,260
Who is it?

110
00:05:31,900 --> 00:05:33,658
Who told you to come here?

111
00:05:33,659 --> 00:05:35,859
Didn't I already say not
to contact me unless necessary?

112
00:05:36,339 --> 00:05:38,299
Living in a dump like this,

113
00:05:38,979 --> 00:05:40,859
and you still dare claim
you married Mr. Huo?

114
00:05:41,140 --> 00:05:42,380
Xu Nange,

115
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:44,178
have you become a scam artist now?

116
00:05:44,179 --> 00:05:45,619
Where's the marriage certificate?

117
00:05:45,779 --> 00:05:48,098
You wouldn't let me see it before.
Take it out.

118
00:05:48,099 --> 00:05:50,220
I'm exposing your lies right now.

119
00:05:50,339 --> 00:05:52,019
What's wrong with you two?

120
00:05:52,020 --> 00:05:53,179
Get out.

121
00:05:53,779 --> 00:05:55,178
Why are you nervous?

122
00:05:55,179 --> 00:05:57,418
Show us the marriage certificate.

123
00:05:57,419 --> 00:05:59,819
Not only
did you fool people at Huo Group,

124
00:05:59,820 --> 00:06:02,379
you even lied
to your university advisor.

125
00:06:02,380 --> 00:06:03,218
Let me tell you.

126
00:06:03,219 --> 00:06:04,778
I've already figured you out, Xu Nange.

127
00:06:04,779 --> 00:06:07,499
If you really are Mrs. Huo,

128
00:06:07,659 --> 00:06:09,379
then call Huo Beiyan over

129
00:06:09,380 --> 00:06:11,218
and let him save you from this mess.

130
00:06:11,219 --> 00:06:12,299
Right?

131
00:06:13,219 --> 00:06:15,220
Why should I call him?

132
00:06:19,339 --> 00:06:20,259
We have visitors?

133
00:06:20,260 --> 00:06:20,899
Mr... Mr. Huo?

134
00:06:20,900 --> 00:06:21,899
Mr. Huo.

135
00:06:21,900 --> 00:06:23,299
Mr. Huo.

136
00:06:25,179 --> 00:06:27,099
They are my stepmother and my sister.

137
00:06:27,900 --> 00:06:29,340
Then sit.

138
00:06:29,859 --> 00:06:31,940
I bought enough groceries
for four people anyway.

139
00:06:32,060 --> 00:06:33,179
Wait, what?

140
00:06:35,179 --> 00:06:35,778
When did I say

141
00:06:35,779 --> 00:06:37,340
I was keeping them for dinner?

142
00:06:37,539 --> 00:06:39,140
That really is Mr. Huo?

143
00:06:47,620 --> 00:06:48,459
Mr. Huo,

144
00:06:48,460 --> 00:06:49,379
why are you living

145
00:06:49,380 --> 00:06:50,459
in a place this rundown?

146
00:06:50,460 --> 00:06:51,658
Did Xu Nange force you?

147
00:06:51,659 --> 00:06:52,298
Just tell me.

148
00:06:52,299 --> 00:06:53,499
I'll teach her a lesson for you.

149
00:06:53,500 --> 00:06:54,499
Where my wife and I live

150
00:06:54,500 --> 00:06:56,059
is none of your business.

151
00:06:57,299 --> 00:06:58,539
Nange, dear,

152
00:06:58,620 --> 00:06:59,738
have some water.

153
00:06:59,739 --> 00:07:00,859
Calm down a little.

154
00:07:05,979 --> 00:07:07,259
You two carry on.

155
00:07:07,260 --> 00:07:08,460
I'm going back to eating.

156
00:07:10,779 --> 00:07:11,579
Xu Yin,

157
00:07:11,580 --> 00:07:13,179
watch your manners.

158
00:07:13,979 --> 00:07:14,459
Mom!

159
00:07:14,460 --> 00:07:15,538
What "Mom"?

160
00:07:15,539 --> 00:07:17,459
Learn something from Nange.

161
00:07:17,460 --> 00:07:18,459
When you eat,

162
00:07:18,460 --> 00:07:20,099
focus on eating properly.

163
00:07:20,620 --> 00:07:21,738
Right, Nange?

164
00:07:21,739 --> 00:07:22,658
Eat more.

165
00:07:22,659 --> 00:07:23,418
Look at you.

166
00:07:23,419 --> 00:07:24,700
You've gotten thinner.

167
00:07:25,099 --> 00:07:25,939
Maybe I've been...

168
00:07:25,940 --> 00:07:27,820
This braised pork is really good.

169
00:07:30,859 --> 00:07:33,460
...a little too strict with you before.

170
00:07:35,099 --> 00:07:36,460
Then eat more.

171
00:07:38,979 --> 00:07:40,419
You're all so loud.

172
00:07:41,060 --> 00:07:42,140
Just eat.

173
00:07:44,299 --> 00:07:46,098
Mom, I feel wronged.

174
00:07:46,099 --> 00:07:47,139
Wronged about what?

175
00:07:47,140 --> 00:07:48,298
Shut up and eat.

176
00:07:48,299 --> 00:07:49,659
I already said you're too noisy.

177
00:07:50,060 --> 00:07:51,140
I...

178
00:07:54,219 --> 00:07:56,979
I have huge news for you.

179
00:07:59,099 --> 00:08:00,298
Our Nange

180
00:08:00,299 --> 00:08:01,978
married the eldest son
of the Huo family,

181
00:08:01,979 --> 00:08:03,499
Huo Beiyan.

182
00:08:03,859 --> 00:08:05,340
What other Huo family could there be?

183
00:08:05,420 --> 00:08:07,499
How many people in Hai City
dare carry the surname Huo?

184
00:08:07,900 --> 00:08:08,939
Why would I lie to you?

185
00:08:08,940 --> 00:08:10,499
What would I gain from it?

186
00:08:10,500 --> 00:08:12,418
They are very lovey-dovey.

187
00:08:12,419 --> 00:08:15,260
They're perfectly happy living together
in that tiny apartment downtown.

188
00:08:15,419 --> 00:08:16,260
Where's that?

189
00:08:16,460 --> 00:08:17,579
That's where our Nange

190
00:08:17,580 --> 00:08:19,459
used to lock herself away for research,

191
00:08:19,460 --> 00:08:22,419
studying day and night like
those old scholars burning midnight oil.

192
00:08:23,979 --> 00:08:25,499
Very admirable, really.

193
00:08:35,140 --> 00:08:36,739
Do you even realize

194
00:08:36,740 --> 00:08:38,499
they never actually left Hai City?

195
00:08:39,260 --> 00:08:40,540
Answer my question.

196
00:08:41,699 --> 00:08:42,779
Understood.

197
00:08:43,020 --> 00:08:44,578
I'm giving you three hours.

198
00:08:44,579 --> 00:08:46,058
Bring the two of them back.

199
00:08:46,059 --> 00:08:47,219
If they don't return,

200
00:08:47,220 --> 00:08:48,700
then neither should you.

201
00:08:48,980 --> 00:08:49,938
But sir, three hours...

202
00:08:49,939 --> 00:08:50,899
Go!

203
00:08:51,900 --> 00:08:52,458
Yes,

204
00:08:52,459 --> 00:08:53,899
right away.

205
00:08:53,980 --> 00:08:55,178
Mr. Huo, ma'am,

206
00:08:55,179 --> 00:08:56,658
please just come back with me.

207
00:08:56,659 --> 00:08:58,298
The old master specifically ordered it.

208
00:08:58,299 --> 00:08:58,899
I...

209
00:08:58,900 --> 00:08:59,940
I'm not going back.

210
00:08:59,980 --> 00:09:01,739
I'm perfectly comfortable here.
Why go back?

211
00:09:01,740 --> 00:09:04,339
Mr. Huo, you don't understand
how angry the old master is right now.

212
00:09:04,340 --> 00:09:06,619
If you don't return,
I won't be able to explain myself.

213
00:09:06,620 --> 00:09:07,820
How about you head back first?

214
00:09:08,179 --> 00:09:09,859
I'll go home after my dad cools down.

215
00:09:09,860 --> 00:09:10,880
Not a chance.

216
00:09:10,880 --> 00:09:13,178
You think I'm going back alone
while you stay here?

217
00:09:13,179 --> 00:09:14,058
Absolutely not.

218
00:09:14,059 --> 00:09:14,979
Either we both go back,

219
00:09:14,980 --> 00:09:15,979
or neither of us does.

220
00:09:15,980 --> 00:09:17,398
- Let's talk this through.
- I was just...

221
00:09:17,398 --> 00:09:18,460
What are you two doing?

222
00:09:21,299 --> 00:09:22,019
Old Master!

223
00:09:22,020 --> 00:09:23,220
Why are you here?

224
00:09:23,459 --> 00:09:25,938
Didn't you say three hours?
It hasn't been three hours yet.

225
00:09:25,939 --> 00:09:27,619
You're hopeless, kid.

226
00:09:27,620 --> 00:09:29,259
I had to come personally.

227
00:09:29,500 --> 00:09:30,420
Dad.

228
00:09:30,900 --> 00:09:31,820
Nange.

229
00:09:32,260 --> 00:09:33,180
Beiyan.

230
00:09:33,459 --> 00:09:34,460
Look at this place.

231
00:09:34,579 --> 00:09:37,220
Why make yourselves suffer
living somewhere like this?

232
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:39,440
What are you standing around for?

233
00:09:39,440 --> 00:09:40,339
Pack your things

234
00:09:40,340 --> 00:09:41,619
and come home with me.

235
00:09:45,779 --> 00:09:46,859
Did you even suffer?

236
00:09:47,100 --> 00:09:48,658
There's not even a proper bed here.

237
00:09:48,659 --> 00:09:49,979
Come on, start packing.

238
00:09:49,980 --> 00:09:52,899
I know. If you hate it so much, don't stay.
Who asked you to stay anyway?

239
00:09:52,900 --> 00:09:53,979
Mind your own business.

240
00:10:00,140 --> 00:10:01,779
You're still worried about Zichen?

241
00:10:04,860 --> 00:10:06,580
Leave it to time.

242
00:10:06,620 --> 00:10:08,019
Accepting our marriage

243
00:10:08,020 --> 00:10:09,139
will take time.

244
00:10:09,900 --> 00:10:12,000
Accepting the way we live together
will also take time.

245
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:13,259
And when we eventually divorce,

246
00:10:13,459 --> 00:10:15,040
it'll tear open his wounds
all over again.

247
00:10:15,040 --> 00:10:17,240
Those three blows combined
will need a long time to soften

248
00:10:17,240 --> 00:10:18,720
if we want to minimize the damage.

249
00:10:18,720 --> 00:10:19,460
So...

250
00:10:20,980 --> 00:10:22,619
I want you
to promise me something first.

251
00:10:22,620 --> 00:10:24,259
Until the timing is right,

252
00:10:24,340 --> 00:10:26,259
maintain things as they are
for as long as possible.

253
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:27,940
How long are we talking?

254
00:10:28,939 --> 00:10:30,619
What's the longest you could accept?

255
00:10:35,579 --> 00:10:37,640
Mr. Huo, the old madam's condition
is acting up again.

256
00:10:37,640 --> 00:10:38,760
Please hurry and check on her.

257
00:11:01,525 --> 00:11:05,299
♪What destiny brought us to meet♪

258
00:11:05,300 --> 00:11:08,474
♪Two different worlds, a love so sweet♪

259
00:11:08,475 --> 00:11:11,870
♪A wish we made
in a past life, it seems♪

260
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:14,854
♪Destined to cross time and dream ♪

261
00:11:14,855 --> 00:11:18,695
♪Like a fairytale story told♪

262
00:11:18,775 --> 00:11:22,032
♪A gentle breeze feels so bold♪

263
00:11:22,050 --> 00:11:25,611
♪As your hair brushes past your ear♪

264
00:11:25,612 --> 00:11:27,949
♪I long to kiss your cheek, my dear♪

265
00:11:27,950 --> 00:11:32,189
♪All my longing, all my love for you♪

266
00:11:32,190 --> 00:11:34,750
♪Has never changed, it's forever true♪

267
00:11:35,162 --> 00:11:41,560
♪It's the hand of fate
that we meet again♪

268
00:11:42,325 --> 00:11:46,763
♪Let me hold you once again♪

269
00:11:47,062 --> 00:11:49,982
♪Resting against your chest♪

270
00:11:50,362 --> 00:11:55,636
♪Your warmth shines like stars at night♪

271
00:11:55,637 --> 00:12:00,461
♪Let me kiss you once again♪

272
00:12:00,462 --> 00:12:03,336
♪No reason needed♪

273
00:12:03,337 --> 00:12:05,534
♪My heart belongs to you♪

274
00:12:05,535 --> 00:12:11,255
♪I'm not afraid
to cross time to find you♪

